To install the current package, make sure you have Python 3.7 or greater installed. 

First, create a virtual environment, running: 
    $python3 -m venv .venv     #N.B ‘.venv’ generic hidden directory name

Activate the virtual environment:
    $source .venv/bin/activate

Then, to install the package with its requirements do: 
    $python3 -m pip install .

Later, to exit the virtual environment, simply do:
    $deactivate
